data.title: Frequently Requested Documents (U.S. National Park Service)
data.text:
Frequent Reports

FOIA Request Log Reports

FOIA Logs are fiscal reports of FOIA requests submitted to the National Park Service. Each log is a compiled Common Separate Value (CSV.) file from October 1 to September 30 for the respective year. To access, click on the desired year to download. The asterisk (*) indicates a change in the electronic tracking system used that resulted in a shift of field names or format however did not affect the data collection.

2015, 2016, 2017, 2018, 2019, 2020 Part 1*, 2020 Part 2*, 2021, 2022, 2023

NPS Mortality Data Reports

The Public Risk Management Program (PRMP) Mortality data is a compiled MS Excel file from CY2007 to CY2023. It is a dynamic report that provides updates based on data available at the time of the report creation.

CY2007 to CY2023 with Expanded Environmental Causes (Released August 2023)
